    "created_at": "2020-06-29T16:33:32Z",
    "updated_at": "2020-06-29T16:33:32Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "`RpcModuleProvider` class is responsible for loading modules that are approved. Currently we allow to enable / disable whole modules in order to avoid risk of exposing potentially dangerous operations to public. \r\nWe should define the subset of safe modules to be enabled by default and require unsafe modules to be explicitly enabled via configuration by users.\r\n\r\nWe should enable `JSON RPC` method level controls (so we can say that for example `eth_getBlockByNumber` can be called via `WebSockets` and `HTTP` and 'eth_sign' can only be called via [IPC](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inter-process_communication). Please note that IPC support needs to be added and will be part of a separate task.",
